        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Bankhead, or near
Atlanta, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Douglasville, City of South Fulton, Sandy Springs, Smyrna,
East Point, Austell, Midtown, Grant Park-Zoo Atlanta, Vinings, Sweet
Auburn, Piedmont Park, Cascade Heights, Lakewood Park, Sandtown,
Atlantic Station, Mableton, Chastain Memorial Park, West End, and
Virginia Highland.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
